Text Count: 2336, reading time is about 4 minutes

Guide reading: THE PRESSURE IS, staff wages, social security costs, logistics costs are also high, in addition, medical protective clothing accessories are about to be used up, but the upstream enterprise resume work rate is still low, difficult to purchase.

By Chen Hongjie

February 26 is the 33rd day after the Spring Festival and the 33rd day of the year of the rat, a protective clothing company in Zhejiang Province.

As early as December twenty-nine before the festival, the boss Zheng Yi suddenly received a call from the local government related staff, "the epidemic is serious, urgent need protective clothing, " so he rushed back to the factory overnight. New Year's Eve, mobilization of Workers; New Year's Day, back to work.

Zheng Yi told China business news that the factory currently produces more than 2,000 sets of protective clothing for medical use every day. On the second day of the Lunar New Year, Huangyan Agricultural and Commercial Bank of Taizhou, Zhejiang, provided an interest-free loan of 5 million yuan. There was no short-term shortage of funds. The pressure is big, the wages of employees, social security expenses, logistics costs are also high, in addition, medical protective clothing accessories are about to run out, but the upstream re-work rate is still low, difficult to purchase.

Shortage of excipients

Zheng Yi has two enterprises, one export-oriented, the other is the domestic sales of Taizhou Huangyan Yiman Industry and Trade Co. , Ltd. ("Yiman Industry and Trade") .

Before the festival, he received a notice to return to work against the epidemic. "On the morning of Lunar New Year's Eve, I attended the local government anti-epidemic conference. In the afternoon, I started to call the local workers with the workshop director and communicated repeatedly to resume work until the evening, " Zheng said.

On the first day of the New Year, more than 50 employees came. Zheng said the first day was mainly for the installation, commissioning and maintenance of machines and related assembly lines. "local governments attach great importance to the prevention and control of the epidemic. At first, there was a shortage of factory cooks, and the street office sent cooks to help Cook for the staff. We also sent Security Assistance, daily staff temperature and plant areas, workshops and other places disinfection, so that workers safe production. Starting from the second day of the Lunar New Year, all the workers are arranged to stay in a hotel,"Zheng said.

At the beginning of the project, we produced two different types of protective clothing, one is the community protection, checkpoint, factory-type ordinary protective clothing, the other is the first-line hospital medical protective clothing. To the seventh day of the Eighth Day of the first lunar month, the daily production of 4000 sets of these two types of protective clothing, mainly ordinary protective clothing.

Later, the need for protective clothing became more pressing. Yiman industry and trade after February 5, on the first general protective clothing production, only do medical protective clothing, the daily output is more than 2,000 sets.

Zheng Yi told China business news that, in general, it takes more than 10 processes to produce a medical protective clothing, from fabric cutting to plastic strips, zippers, elastics, inspection, packaging and quality inspection.

The main materials for producing medical protective clothing are sufficient, but the auxiliary materials will be in short supply soon, and the logistics cost is also under great pressure. Zheng Yi said that the main materials stored enough, and accessories, such as zippers, thread, tape, elastic tape and other reserves are not much. Now most upstream enterprises have not resumed work, auxiliary materials in short supply, prices have also begun to rise, some auxiliary materials suppliers put forward a price increase of 15% .

Spending pressure

Under the epidemic situation, the small and medium-sized enterprise's wage and the social security pressure is not small. "during the Spring Festival, workers are paid three times their normal wages, " says Zheng. Companies pay social security for 35 percent of workers stranded in their hometowns.

In order to fully support Yiman Industry and trade to produce medical protective clothing, Zheng Yi also from his foreign trade export company to mobilize staff, and the company temporarily suspended production. As a result of foreign trade export company employees slightly higher wages, the overall cost increase. Moreover, since protective clothing is a strategic material, the combined profit of the two companies is down about 30% to 40% compared with the same period last year.

In addition, the cost of logistics is also a lot of pressure. Zheng Yi said that under the epidemic, the logistics transportation is the hair air transportation, before a batch of rubber strip's land transportation price only several hundred yuan, air transportation about one thousand yuan. Recently, the factory bought three batches of tape, and the cost of air freight was 12,000 yuan.

Recently, Taizhou issued "ten opinions on speeding up the production of epidemic prevention and control materials. " Encouraging enterprises engaged in the production of epidemic prevention emergency supplies incorporated into the unified requisition and allocation of provinces and municipalities, and enterprises engaged in the transformation of production of epidemic prevention emergency supplies incorporated into the unified requisition and allocation of provinces and municipalities, and giving priority to expanding production capacity and technological transformation, the funds for emergency technical transformation shall be subsidized by 50% of the investment in equipment, with a maximum of 2 million yuan. The funds required shall actively seek the relevant subsidies from the higher authorities and be financed by the municipal funds for Epidemic Prevention and control; and the research and development of new products for epidemic prevention and control shall be increased, after the new product is on the market, depending on the actual situation, the municipal special fund for Science and Technology will give a certain amount of reward.

"We support the production of protective clothing, face masks, goggles, disinfection products, electronic thermometers and other epidemic prevention and control materials. The local government shall, according to state regulations, subsidize the overtime wages of the employees of enterprises producing epidemic prevention emergency materials that are unified requisitioned and allocated at the provincial and municipal levels,"the document said.

Well-funded

Zheng said there would be no major plant renovation and land acquisition in the first half of this year, adding that Huangyan agricultural and Commercial Bank has recently granted a 5 million Yuan interest-free credit loan, so there is no shortage of funds in the short term.

"On the morning of the 2nd day of the Lunar New Year, the chairman of the Huangyan agricultural and Commercial Bank, along with the business department and the staff of the sub-branch, went to the factory to investigate the capital requirements, opened an account at noon, and in the afternoon, the bank's credit granting and approval departments were approved. Before 4:30, the bank's 5 million yuan loan funds arrived in the company's account. You know, Yiman Industry and trade has not done business with Huangyan agricultural firm before,"Zheng said.

On February 24, the general manager of the Subsidiary Department of Huangyan Agricultural and Commercial Bank told China business news that, "The whole bank fully supports msmes to start their business in an orderly manner. As long as the enterprises have loan needs, we will handle it as a special matter and close it on the same day. This afternoon, the loan review and approval meeting approved the financing needs of five smes. "

The above-mentioned agricultural and Commercial Bank told the financial reporter, in order to support the resumption of production, Huangyan agricultural and Commercial Bank of the "Financial Services Eight special measures notice. ". A special credit product "return to work and production credit" was created, and 1 billion yuan of funds was earmarked to support enterprises, individual industrial and commercial households and rural households affected by the epidemic to return to work and production, of which 500 million were targeted at enterprises in distress, to help solve the problem of fund shortage during the anti-epidemic period, the interest rate of the loans will be as low as 4.15% , and the maximum loan amount will be 10 million yuan for the public and 5 million yuan for the private sector. The new loans granted in February will enjoy one-month (30-day) interest-free concessions.

Furthermore, the interest payable on loans for the month of February 2020 will not exceed the current LPR interest rate of 4.15 per cent for enterprises heavily affected by the epidemic, such as those in the manufacturing, wholesale and retail sectors, accommodation and catering sectors, after verification by the bank, the difference has been collected to return; the implementation of loan extension. Automatic extension of 120 days for loans (except installment loans) maturing from February 10 to 29, and 30 days for installment loans; charging of interest at the original contract interest rate during the extension period without penalty interest; opening up a Green Channel on-line, the bank applies for loans through the Taizhou credit information sharing platform of the central branch of the People's Bank of China in Taizhou, the palm-based lending platform of the Taizhou Banking and Insurance Regulatory Bureau, and the bank's wechat account.

"As of February 23,286 enterprises and 2,385 enterprises have been listed as key support enterprises for emergency supplies and 2,347 million yuan of loans have been granted to enterprises for emergency supplies, 9,199 million yuan of loans have been granted to enterprises providing support for key living materials, and 699 million yuan of new loans have been granted during the epidemic, " the head of the Agricultural Credit Union of Zhejiang Province also told China Business News.
